attributes.title: Ep. 1 Sathya Sai Baba: Green Diamonds
attributes.description: In the first episode of Cult Podcast, original hosts Paige and Marie take a deep dive into the world of Sathya Sai Baba, his alleged miracles, and the controversies surrounding his ashrams and schools.

attributes.title: Ep. 136 The Branch Davidians Pt. 1: Ruby Ridge
attributes.description: We're celebrating 1,000,000 downloads by kicking off a series that's been a long time comin'. With all the craziness surrounding the Branch Davidian's compound and violent end, it's important that we take a look at why the Feds were all shaken up. Just 9 months before everyone in America would know the town of Waco, TX, another standoff was underway. Join us as Paige takes Mando and Andrea through the Weaver Family's story and we learn why everyone was so on edge.

attributes.title: Ep. 137 The Branch Davidians Pt. 2: God’s Honor Roll
attributes.description: We're back with the second installment of our series on The Branch Davidians, David Koresh, and the Waco Siege. Last week Paige took Mando and Andrea through what the US Government had been going through. Join us this week as she breaks down the origins of the group that Koresh would eventually take control of. Plus you get to learn about the worst stained glass window in the history of windows.

attributes.title: Ep. 138 The Branch Davidians Pt. 3: The Real Ph.D.
attributes.description: We're back with another installment in our series on David Koresh and the Branch Davidians! This week, Paige takes Mando and Andrea through David's arrival, love of music, and rise to power. Join us to learn all about the Devil's Salad and the TRUE explanation of what a "Ph.D." is.

attributes.title: Ep. 139 The Branch Davidians Pt. 4: Ladies Night at The Lord’s House
attributes.description: We're back with another installment in our series on The Branch Davidians and David Koresh! Join us this week as Paige takes Mando and Andrea through life inside the compound. Why were tensions so high? What did they do for money? What on earth is a "Berry Pouch"?! Tune in to find out!

attributes.title: Ep. 140 The Branch Davidians Pt. 5: Catch Me If You Can Pt. BOO
attributes.description: We're back with the final installment in our series on The Branch Davidians, David Koresh, and Waco. Join us this week as Paige takes Mando and Andrea through the Seige at Waco and how this tragedy could've been prevented by both sides multiple different times. This one is most definitely rough, and weirdly relevant, but we promise that it's worth the listen. Also, we rollin' with Oprah now. So, we're pretty much demi-Gods.

attributes.title: Ep. 141 Antifa: Ropes of Justice
attributes.description: We're back this week to talk about a group that's been on everyone's mind lately. Join us as Mando tells Paige and Andrea about Antifascism, Antifa for short. You'll learn all about the group's origins, why they started, and why it's so troubling to have them labelled as a "terrorist organization". The metaphors are strong with this episode.

attributes.title: Ep. 142 Timothy McVeigh: Meat Cute
attributes.description: We’re back this week with the first installment in our series on Timothy McVeigh and the Oklahoma City Bombing. The story behind the 1995 attack is almost common knowledge now. An angry white kid got so upset with our government that he decided to send a gruesome message. But what made Timothy so perfect for radicalization? Join us as Mando tells Paige and Andrea all about the goofy childhood that helped push him into becoming the deadliest domestic terrorist in modern American history.

attributes.title: Ep. 143 Timothy McVeigh Pt. 2: Gun Baby
attributes.description: Join us as Mando takes Paige and Andrea through Timothy McVeigh's time in the Army, his first two killings, and the start of his radicalization. We all know where this is headed, but did you know about the part where he LITERALLY let Jesus take the wheel? Yeah. Didn't think so.

attributes.title: Ep. 144 Timothy McVeigh Pt. 3: Free Range Guns
attributes.description: We're back this week with the final installment in our series on Timothy McVeigh. Join us as Mando takes Paige and Andrea through the last leg of Tim's trip toward radicalization. Come find out how interconnected these events really were. Fair warning, this one does get rough. But there's still some top notch goofing' throughout it, too!

attributes.title: Ep. 145 The Sacrament (Feat. Horror Virgin)
attributes.description: Armando and Andrea are on Vacation so Mikey and Todd from Horror Virgin join Paige for an extra special episode as we review The Sacrament, a movie that's basically Jonestown, without officially being Jonestown. Join in for some laughs and we'll be back together for a normal episode next week.

attributes.title: Ep. 146 Sylvester Graham: Cracker, Please
attributes.description: The gang is all here! We're back from vacation! This week we dive into the delicious, although sexually repressed, history of the Graham Cracker and Sylvester Graham's crusade against bad bread, jerking off, and infrequent dumps. It's a blast and you'll never look at s'mores the same way again.

attributes.title: Ep. 147 John Kellogg: Take You To The Broom Factory
attributes.description: We're back this week with a "sort-of" continuation of last week's episode. One of Sylvester Graham's followers later became well known for his "health retreat" that served a "flakey corn treat". Join us as Paige takes Mando and Andrea through the life and inventions of John Harvey Kellogg.

attributes.title: Ep. 148 Mary Baker Eddy: Brain Too Big
attributes.description: We're back this week continuing our "series" on weird "medicine" from the past. Tune in to hear Paige take Mando and Andrea through the life of Mary Baker Eddy and the plethora of wild characters that inhabit her life's story. And if that don't thrill you, we got Jesus juggling and chainsaws this week! You read that right. It's a crazy fun time!

attributes.title: Ep. 149 America’s Frontline Doctors: Send Fauci’s Pee (Ft. Good Morning From Hell)
attributes.description: Stop the presses, we've got some breaking cult news! Last week a video went viral, for SEVERAL reasons, and there's so much to unpack here we decided to make it an entire episode. And here to help us understand it are resident sex-demon experts, Blaine Gibson and Chris Demarais from the podcast Good Morning From Hell!

attributes.title: Ep. 150 Chen Tao: A Very Nutty Episode
attributes.description: We're back this week with a story so crazy it's OuT oF tHiS wOrLd! Sort of. Join us as Mando takes Paige and Andrea through the beginnings of Chen Tao and their crazy mishmash of beliefs. Also, Paige creates the #PaintBallChallenge and you DO NOT want to miss out.

attributes.title: Ep. 151 Chen Tao Pt. 2: Again Tao
attributes.description: We're back this week to close out our series on a wild Taiwanese doomsday cult. Last time we covered their insane origins, this time we dive into their unbelievable publicity stunts. Strap in folks, this one gets WEIRD!

attributes.title: Ep. 152 Adidam: Guru Fight
attributes.description: We're back this week to talk about what happens when Gurus can't get along. Join us for frank discussions about what body parts do what, and learn Armando's new name!

attributes.title: Ep. 153: Multi-Level Marketing: Buttery Soft
attributes.description: Hey Hun, we have a business opportunity for you. You can stay home, choose your own hours, and listen to Cult Podcast whenever you want! Join us on our journey through the world of Multi-Level Marketing and all the pitfalls and cult-like behavior that follows.

attributes.title: Ep. 154 Flordelis Dos Santos: You’ve Got Crabs
attributes.description: Today we’re covering Flordelis Dos Santos and her bizarre cult of adoption and questionable family relationships. Join us this week to unravel her most recent news controversies and find out what’s crabs got to do with it?

attributes.title: Ep. 155 Hell’s Angels: Metallic Horse Girls
attributes.description: We're back this week to tell you the story of one of America's most infamous groups. And possibly the loudest and most annoying, too. Join us as Paige takes Mando and Andrea through the early history of the Hell's Angels and early motorcycle culture. You don't really have a choice. This is a rebellion you can't refuse!

attributes.title: Ep. 156 Hell’s Angels Pt. 2: $500 Worth of Beer
attributes.description: We're back this week for part two of our series on the Hell's Angels! Join us as Paige takes Mando and Andrea through the formative years of the gang and their first big legendary tale. This star-studded episode will have you asking, "What would you do for $500 Worth of Beer?"

attributes.title: Ep. 157 Hell’s Angels Pt. 3 Tony “Truth” Taint
attributes.description: We're back with another installment in our series on the Hell's Angels. Join us as Paige takes Mando and Andre through the fast and hard lives of Sonny's club of drug traffickers. How did the Angels build such a sophisticated syndicate? You'll have to listen to find out!

attributes.title: Ep. 158 Hell’s Angels Pt. 4: Fireworks for Knives
attributes.description: LAAAAAADIEEEES! We're back with the final installment in our series on the Hell's Angels. Tune in to hear Paige walk Mando and Andrea through the snitches, stitches, and all around hitches (in plans) that surround America's most infamous biker gang. This one brought to you by the plumbing department at your local Home Depot.

attributes.title: Ep. 159 Church of God with Signs Following: Are You CNNing This?
attributes.description: We're back with another ssssuper fun episssode! Join us as Paige tells Mando and Andrea all about a crazy group of Jesus loving, moonshine pounding, snake dancing weirdos and their insane fugitive leader. This ones more fun than a barrel of snakes. Mostly because everything is more fun than a barrel of snakes.

attributes.title: Ep. 160 OneTaste: Breadbowls From Artby’s
attributes.description: We're back this week with a rare Andrea episode! Join us as the Unicorn Queen herself takes Paige and Mando through a sex cult with some interesting twists and turns. Bonus: You get to learn way a piece of intimate Andrea history.

attributes.title: Ep. 161 OneTaste Pt. 2: ChickenLube.biz
attributes.description: We're back this week with the GRIPPING conclusion to our series on OneTaste. Join us as Andrea takes Paige and Mando through everything going absolutely buck wild. Also join us as we develop the best website/business idea of ALL TIME! Throw a copyright all over this episode baybee!

attributes.title: Ep. 162 Donald Trump Pt. 1: The Poodle Dog
attributes.description: We're back this week with one of our most anticipated episodes to date. The 45th President of the United States is one of the most divisive figures in modern history. It has long been said that he has a cult-like following, but how literal is that description? In this series we will breakdown the legacy, history, and political career of Donald "Jeezy" Trump. Get ready. It's gonna be a wild ride.

attributes.title: Ep. 163 Donald Trump Pt. 2: Swordfish Balloons
attributes.description: We're back to continue our series on Donald Trump and the MAGA Cult. When we left off last week, Mando was walking Paige and Andrea through the death of Friedrich Trump. Join us this week as we find out what life lessons the Bavarian barber imparted on his son Frederick Christ Trump. Get the yacht ready and grab some earplugs. It's about to go down.

attributes.title: Ep. 163 Donald Trump Pt. 3: Don King with Worse Hair
attributes.description: We're back this week with the third installment of our series on Donald Trump and the MAGA Cult. Join us as Mando tells Paige and Andrea all about Donny's youth and early adulthood. Learn all about his intense sibling rivalry. And prepare to groan loudly. A lot. This one is infuriating.

attributes.title: Interview with Jordan Coburn: Every 15 Minutes
attributes.description: We're taking a break this week to unbuckle our belts and pretend to lag out of family Zoom calls. However, it doesn't mean we're letting Trump off the hook. Joining us this week is Jordan Coburn, host of "I Disagree" and "Mueller, She Wrote". We sit down and talk all about Trump and what it felt to cover the man's crimes for so long.

attributes.title: Cult News & Paula White: The Blessed Chain
attributes.description: In order to prepare for another lockdown Paige, Mando, and Andrea needed to take a breather. Join us this week as we cover cult news and the story of our president's "spiritual advisor" Paula White. Yep. It gets wild FAST.
